 Find the value of $f(-2)$.
\begin{align*}
f(x) &= \frac{3x-2}{x-2} \\
f(-2) &= \frac{3(-2)-2}{-2-2} \\
&= \frac{-6-2}{-2-2} \\
&= \frac{-8}{-4} \\
&= 2
\end{align*}

## Step 2: Find the value of $f(-1)$.
\begin{align*}
f(x) &= \frac{3x-2}{x-2} \\
f(-1) &= \frac{3(-1)-2}{-1-2} \\
&= \frac{-3-2}{-1-2} \\
&= \frac{-5}{-3} \\
&= \frac{5}{3}
\end{align*}

## Step 3: Find the value of $f(0)$.
\begin{align*}
f(x) &= \frac{3x-2}{x-2} \\
f(0) &= \frac{3(0)-2}{0-2} \\
&= \frac{0-2}{0-2} \\
&= \frac{-2}{-2} \\
&= 1
\end{align*}

## Step 4: Calculate $f(-2) + f(-1) + f(0)$.
\begin{align*}
f(-2) + f(-1) + f(0) &= 2 + \frac{5}{3} + 1 \\
&= 2 + \frac{5}{3} + 1 \\
&= \frac{6}{3} + \frac{5}{3} + \frac{3}{3} \\
&= \frac{14}{3}
\end{align*}
Therefore, the final answer is: $\boxed{\frac{14}{3}}$.
